<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="757" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="29.[1367,2572,269,428]" pageId="29" pageNumber="757">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1369,1718,269,302]" pageId="29" pageNumber="757">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Kinabalu Squirrel is widely distributed, occurs in a number of protected areas, and presents a stable trend. There are no known threats to the population.
</paragraph>
